Diagnosis.
This small frog has: (
1
) skin on dorsum smooth, that on belly areolate; dorsolateral folds absent; pair of dorsal protrusions in sacral region and small pair in scapular region; discoidal fold not evident; (
2
) tympanic membrane differentiated; tympanic annulus low, smooth, round, its diameter about 
40
% length of eye; (
3
